# Bernard Bolter Archive ‚Äî Cursor Rules

## Workspace safety

This workspace contains two repos:
- `bernardbolter-new` ‚Äî the active Next.js + Tailwind + Payload CMS repo. **Write here only.**
- `bernardbolter-sass-old` ‚Äî the legacy WordPress/Sass repo. **Read only. Never create, edit, or delete any file in this folder.**

If a task requires reading an old component, read it. Do not modify it.

---

## Stack

- Next.js (App Router)
- Tailwind CSS
- Payload CMS
- Neon (Postgres)
- TypeScript throughout

---

## Tailwind ‚Äî hard rules

- **Never use default Tailwind breakpoints** (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`). This project uses custom breakpoints only: `s:` (550px), `m:` (768px), `l:` (979px), `xl:` (1200px).
- Font sizes and spacing in `rem`, not `px`. Exceptions: 1‚Äì2px borders, SVG strokes, integer grid gaps.
- Do not invent spacing values outside the scale defined in `tailwind.config.ts`.
- Do not add new color values ‚Äî use CSS variables and the token system only.

---

## Z-index ‚Äî named layers only

Never use an arbitrary z-index number. Use only these named layers (defined in `tailwind.config.ts`):

| Layer | Value | Usage |
|---|---|---|
| `z-chrome` | 2000 | Info panel, name container |
| `z-nav` | 3000 | Nav, search nav, filter nav |
| `z-overlay` | 4000 | Artwork image overlays |
| `z-ui-top` | 5000 | Nav buttons, switcher |
| `z-modal` | 6000 | Modals, lightboxes |

---

## Typography

Three fonts, three roles ‚Äî do not swap them:

| Token | Font | Role |
|---|---|---|
| `font-body` | Barlow | Body prose only |
| `font-heading` | Barlow Condensed | Headings, labels, nav, UI text |
| `font-title` | Staatliches | Large display text and panel section labels only |

- Do not use Barlow for headings.
- Do not use Barlow Condensed for body prose.
- Do not use Staatliches for anything other than large display and section labels.
- Do not apply `text-transform: uppercase` globally ‚Äî Staatliches handles this inherently.

---

## Colors

- All colors via CSS variables and the token system. No hardcoded hex values in components.
- Series colors always via `getSeriesColor(slug)` from `src/helpers/seriesColor.ts`. Never hardcode a series color.
- Token naming: `surface-*` for backgrounds, `text-*` for text, `ui-*` for chrome, `series-*` for series accents, `status-*` for form feedback.

---

## Artwork display ‚Äî critical

This site represents artwork at a size that reflects real-world physical scale. This logic must never be violated.

- **Never use `object-cover` on artwork images.** Always `object-contain`.
- **Never normalize artwork display** to fill uniform grid cells.
- **All artwork dimensions via `useArtworkDimensions()`** from `src/hooks/useArtworkDimensions.tsx`. Never hardcode width/height for artwork display.
- Size (`sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`) and orientation (landscape, portrait, square) constraints must both apply simultaneously.
- This logic lives in the hook and the reusable component ‚Äî never duplicated per view.

---

## Scroll containers

All page-level scroll containers must have hidden scrollbars:
```css
overflow: scroll;
scrollbar-width: none;
::-webkit-scrollbar { display: none; }
```

Never use `overflow: hidden` on scroll containers.

---

## Forms

- **Never use `<form>` tags.** Use `div` + `onClick` / `onChange` handlers.

---

## Component patterns

- Series image placeholder backgrounds use `getSeriesColor(slug)` ‚Äî always.
- The `isProgramScroll` ref on timeline scroll handlers must never be removed or refactored. It prevents scroll events firing during programmatic navigation.
- TitleCorner SVG coordinates must not be altered.
- The `ArtworkTitle` component has three modes ‚Äî do not collapse them.

---

## What NOT to do

- ‚ùå Write any file in `bernardbolter-sass-old/`
- ‚ùå Use `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` breakpoints
- ‚ùå Use `object-cover` on artwork images
- ‚ùå Hardcode series colors
- ‚ùå Hardcode artwork dimensions
- ‚ùå Use arbitrary z-index values
- ‚ùå Use `px` for font sizes or spacing (exceptions: borders, SVG strokes, grid gaps)
- ‚ùå Use `overflow: hidden` on scroll containers
- ‚ùå Use `<form>` tags
- ‚ùå Use Barlow Condensed for body prose
- ‚ùå Use Staatliches for anything other than large display text
- ‚ùå Remove or refactor the `isProgramScroll` ref
- ‚ùå Alter TitleCorner SVG coordinates
- ‚ùå Introduce new spacing values not in the scale
- ‚ùå Introduce new breakpoints

